{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/?p=148890", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/05/26/the-future-of-wine-is-changing-the-community-around-it-is-not/", "title": "The Future of Wine Is Changing. The Community Around It Is Not.", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/WISS-2026-Photos-058-scaled-e1779665201909.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" title=\"pleasethepalate.com\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"768\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/WISS-2026-Photos-058-scaled-e1779665201909.jpg\" title=\"pleasethepalate.com\" width=\"1024\" /></p>I have spent more than two decades in the wine industry. And while wine is a product, a commodity, I have never thought of it only as that. Wine tells stories. Each bottle tells the story of a place, culture, family, and history, as well as the year and the people involved in bringing it to life. Some of my closest friendships, most memorable travels, and meaningful conversations have taken place around a table with wine. Wine has always been about connection.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/WISS-2026-Photos-058-scaled-e1779665201909.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" title=\"pleasethepalate.com\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"768\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/WISS-2026-Photos-058-scaled-e1779665201909.jpg\" title=\"pleasethepalate.com\" width=\"1024\" /></p>I have spent more than two decades in the wine industry. And while wine is a product, a commodity, I have never thought of it only as that. Wine tells stories. Each bottle tells the story of a place, culture, family, and history, as well as the year and the people involved in bringing it to life. Some of my closest friendships, most memorable travels, and meaningful conversations have taken place around a table with wine. Wine has always been about connection.", "published_at": "2026-05-26 20:14:08+00:00", "source_name": "Wine Industry Advisor", "source_type": "media", "language": "en", "content_type": "market_report", "country": "US", "continent": "NEW_WORLD", "region": "Americas/North/USA", "producer_role": "trade_media", "trust_tier": "T3_professional", "info_purpose": ["P2_market_analysis"], "collection_tier": "C1_rss"}
